  "text": "The measured expansion rates were grouped into bins, and frequency distributions were constructed. As shown previously [CITATION_1] , the expansion rates are exponentially distributed ( Figure 2 ). The characteristic expansion rates ρ were obtained from single exponential fits to the distributions obtained under the different experimental conditions. In the absence of PMA, the characteristic fusion pore expansion rate in cells stimulated at low [Ca 2ϩ ] i (Figure 2A ) was 28 Ϯ 2 nS/s (n ϭ 354 fusion pores from 38 cells).",
